Subject: [PATCH] Pin MSVC toolset via -vcvars_ver

V8 14.6 needs MSVC >= 14.40 (std::function/base::FunctionRef interop in
bind-internal.h). The VS install default (e.g. 14.38) fails to compile. MSVC
14.x is ABI-cross-compatible, so a 14.44-built lib links fine into UE.
Adjust the version to one installed on the build machine.

Path: build/toolchain/win/setup_toolchain.py  (in the v8 'build' sub-repo)
--- a/build/toolchain/win/setup_toolchain.py
+++ b/build/toolchain/win/setup_toolchain.py
@@ def _LoadToolchainEnv(cpu, toolchain_root, sdk_dir, target_store):
     # packaged toolchain in build/vs_toolchain.py.
     args.append(SDK_VERSION)
+    # Pin MSVC toolset: V8 14.6 needs >=14.40 STL. MSVC 14.x is ABI-cross-
+    # compatible so this links fine into UE.
+    args.append('-vcvars_ver=14.44.35207')
     variables = _LoadEnvFromBat(args)
   return _ExtractImportantEnvironment(variables)
